DamageArbiter - disagreement-driven arbitration

damage_arbiter.py implements the arbitration stage of DamageArbiter. It reads the
out-of-fold (OOF) predictions of the ViT-B/32 image-only baseline and the
CLIP-LLM multimodal baseline and:

  - uses the shared prediction when ViT and CLIP agree;
  - when they disagree, trains a lightweight logistic-regression arbitrator to
    decide which model to trust.

No ground-truth leakage. The final manuscript uses only features computed from
the base models' softmax outputs, so the same feature computation can be applied
to new, unlabeled imagery:

  * confidence  — max-softmax probability (probability of the predicted class)
  * entropy     — Shannon entropy of the softmax distribution
  * margin      — decision margin (top-1 minus top-2 probability)

The label-dependent quantity p_pred - p_true (saved as `error_margin` by the
base-model scripts) is used only for the overconfident/ambiguous error diagnosis,
never as an arbitration feature. The decision threshold is fixed at tau = 0.5.

Run:
  python damage_arbiter.py \
      --vit-oof   oof_vitb32_all.csv \
      --clip-oof  oof_clip_gpt_all.csv

The script prints the feature ablation (all configurations are comparable) and the
final confidence-configuration metrics, and writes per-sample DamageArbiter
predictions to a CSV. The confidence configuration is selected for parsimony and
deployability.

Requires: pandas, numpy, scikit-learn.
